<br>
As for KEI hurting the game:<br>
<br>
I'm in KC with a group doing LCY with my chanter.  The cleric (for once) isn't chain fizzling heal spells and is content NOT to be the main damage dealer by chain stunning mobs with his KEI enhanced mana pool.  So I'm thinking cool, you can have a good group in KC after all.  But no wait!  Our main tank, an SK, seems a bit casting happy.  So I watch.  He pulls with snare, does the complete line of debuffs, terror, and then throws in a dot and a spear dd.....on every single mob.  I'm thinking a'kay he's obviously got kei....sk's don't have that kind of mana pool at that level.  But everythings going smoothly so I write it off buckle down for some exp grinding.<br>
<br>
Then two hours later the sk's kei runs out...he tells our druid he needs a ride to nexus to get kei.  Most of the group complains about it, and the SK get's snippy, and says words to the effect of...if I don't have mana, how do you think I'm suppose to hold agro?<br>
<br>
Oh, I dunno.....Taunt mebbe?<br>
<br>
To which I was promptly told taunt doesn't work, and he thinks he knows his class better then I do, and doesn't appreciate me telling him what do to.<br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
I don't get it...how ever did all those pre KEI Sk's manage to fool us all into thinking they were the reigning gods of agro with taunt and a few well choosen spells?   The Frauds! <br>
<br>
There are people of all levels who use kei and know how to play there class, who have learned to manage agro and their mana pools.  I've seen many of them while grouping with my various alts.  However I've seen many more who are like the sk, and while very good players with kei (and he was a good tank for the group) they are clueless what their class can and can't do without it.  It prolly never occurred to the sk that he could generate just as much agro using far far less mana/spells.  It never occurred to him because he prolly never had a situation where he it became necessary for him to discover it on his own.<br>
<br>
Someone playing their class while buffed to the hilt really isn't any indication of their skill or their game knowledge.  And anyone that says they &quot;can't&quot; play their class without kei&quot;, should just leave it at &quot;they can't play their class.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.orderofthephoenix.com/images/signature/NovPoPsig%20framed.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bethene>Bethene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 1355<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/7/03 6:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.sycornet.com/familjen/images/members/thumb_bethene.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chanters like me caused the War</span><hr size=1> Demad: personally I hand the cleric 10 peridots if I want virtue. Although usually it is a 2 rez-and-vitue package deal in Tactics. =)<br>
